line=348 fonts=F2-10.9,F4-10.9,F4-8.0,F6-10.9,F9-8.0 bbox=36.83,143.16,288.27,156.07:      ii. L_{E} relativizes all speech-acts to the speaker (c_{A}).
line=349 fonts=F2-10.9,F6-10.9,F9-8.0 bbox=34.41,125.92,288.79,138.54 iscore=0.22   :     iii. L_{E} achieves the independence property: phrases
line=350 fonts=F2-10.9 bbox=50.17,114.08,319.39,124.99 iscore=0.12                  :        containing expressive content have at least two logically
line=351 fonts=F2-10.9 bbox=50.17,100.53,271.33,111.44 iscore=0.12                  :        and  compositionally independent denotations.

doc_id=74 page=30 block_id=30-5 bbox=34.67,28.8,326.72,93.91 label=btbb 352 356
line=352 fonts=F2-10.9,F6-10.9,F9-8.0 bbox=34.67,81.29,322.51,93.91:     iv. L_{E} helps us get a grip on descriptive ineffability because
line=353 fonts=F2-10.9 bbox=50.17,69.45,326.72,80.36 iscore=0.10   :        descriptives and expressives operate on different aspects
line=354 fonts=F2-10.9 bbox=50.17,55.9,306.0,66.81 iscore=0.20     :        of the information state: descriptives act on the set of
line=355 fonts=F2-10.9 bbox=50.17,42.35,312.37,53.26 iscore=0.10   :        possible worlds, whereas expressives act on the set of
line=356 fonts=F2-10.9 bbox=50.17,28.8,93.33,39.71 iscore=0.11     :        contexts.

